sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K592017
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This gene consists of the green light sensing protein CcaS along with its response regulator CcaR.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Lei Sun
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: CcaR and CcaS can be found in the genome of Synechocystis sp. PCC6803.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The SYnechocystis sp. codon usage not tuned for expression in E.coli. Strong RBS to ensure expression.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0034
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix.

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info for this part: Brian Chow

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K592001
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: CcaS, green light sensor from Synechocystis sp. PCC6803
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: CcaS is a green light sensor protein from the genome of Synechocystis sp. PCC6803. It requires PCB as the chromophore to function. PCB is made by [[Part:BBa_I15008|ho1]] and [[Part:BBa_I15009|PcyA]]. Furthermore, CcaS works in conjunction with [[Part:BBa_K592002|CcaR]], its response regulator. This is the green light sensor used by Tabor in his multichromatic light-sensing system which composed of CcaS/CcaR and Cph8/EnvZ.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Lei Sun
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This DNA was extracted from Tabor's pJT122 plasmid. Two illegal internal restriction sites had to be removed in order to allow BioBrick-compatibility.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K592002
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: ccaR is the response regulator of the green sensor that also includes the membrane-associated histidine kinase ccaS. The two-componet system is also dependent of a chromophore.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Erik Lundin
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The ccaR was amplified from a pJT118 provided by Voight et al (2011) Multichromatic Control of Gene Expression in Escherichia coli, J. Mol. Biol., 405, p315???324
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The ccaR amplified from pJT118 was point mutated to get rid of illegal restriction site.
